363
00:32:49,244 --> 00:32:51,443
这些可以等选举结束后再讨论
Surely this can wait until after the election.

364
00:32:51,463 --> 00:32:53,963
如果我输了，学这些有什么用？
There's no point learning all this if I lose.

365
00:32:54,033 --> 00:32:55,793
你不会输的
You will not lose.

366
00:32:55,863 --> 00:32:58,793
为什么你这么肯定？还有其它候选人
You're very sure of that. There are other candidates.

367
00:33:01,132 --> 00:33:03,332
我想我警告过你嘲笑我是什么后果
I believe I warned you about mocking me.

368
00:33:03,392 --> 00:33:06,102
请原谅，先生，但我以为你已经了解了这个制度
Forgive me, sir. I had thought you understood the system.

369
00:33:06,162 --> 00:33:09,102
其它候选人都只是凑数的
The other candidates are straw men.

370
00:33:10,051 --> 00:33:11,571
凑数的？
Straw men?

371
00:33:11,901 --> 00:33:14,581
但是如果没有反对者
It saves a great deal of useless strife

372
00:33:14,601 --> 00:33:17,131
当然能够避免无意义的竞争，但只有恺撒的人
if there's no opposition, but it would look ill

373
00:33:17,141 --> 00:33:19,361
站出来又会显得太突兀
if Caesar's man was the only one standing.

374
00:33:22,530 --> 00:33:24,830
这些事实让你困扰吗？
These facts disturb you somehow?

375
00:33:24,900 --> 00:33:27,830
选举是由神圣的朱庇特神监督的
The elections are sanctioned by Jupiter Capitolinus.

376
00:33:27,830 --> 00:33:29,329
选举可是庄严的事情啊
They are sacred.

377
00:33:29,759 --> 00:33:32,899
恺撒也是由朱庇特神指派的，不是吗？
Caesar also is sanctioned by Jupiter, is he not?

378
00:33:32,969 --> 00:33:35,799
有预兆，有胜利的凯旋
By augury, by triumph,

379
00:33:35,869 --> 00:33:37,599
也有人民的拥护
by acclaim of the people.

380
00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:41,698
他所作的一切，都是由神庇护的
Anything he does is sacred.

381
00:33:41,718 --> 00:33:43,698
某种程度上，他就是神本身
In a way, he is a demigod.

382
00:33:43,768 --> 00:33:46,038
仅仅在那一天而已
For one day only.

383
00:33:46,268 --> 00:33:49,167
其它日子里，他和你我一样，都是凡人
For the rest, he is a mortal man like you and me.

384
00:33:49,367 --> 00:33:51,477
不管他是不是凡人，他在试图拯救共和国
Mortal or not, he is trying to save the Republic.

385
00:33:51,487 --> 00:33:53,517
通过贿赂选举？
By corrupting the elections?

386
00:33:53,557 --> 00:33:56,567
罗马人民可没有期盼干净的选举
The Roman people are not crying out for clean elections.

387
00:33:56,577 --> 00:33:58,767
他们期盼的是工作
They are crying out for jobs.

388
00:33:58,787 --> 00:34:00,996
他们期盼的是甘甜的水和食物
They are crying out for clean water, for food,

389
00:34:01,066 --> 00:34:03,296
和平稳定的生活
for stability and peace.

390
00:34:03,566 --> 00:34:06,436
你可以为人们做到这些
You can do great things for your people.

391
00:34:06,496 --> 00:34:08,436
你可以帮助恺撒
You can help

392
00:34:08,496 --> 00:34:10,695
拯救共和国
save the Republic.

393
00:34:14,565 --> 00:34:17,905
或者你可以回到你的小店铺去继续卖你的羊肉跟猪肉
Or you can go back to your shop and resume selling mutton and pig,

394
00:34:17,965 --> 00:34:20,004
满手污泥却保持一颗高尚的心
have dirty hands but a clean conscience.

395
00:34:30,333 --> 00:34:32,333
你怎么想？
So what do you say?

396
00:34:34,163 --> 00:34:35,653
什么？
Say to what?

397
00:34:35,663 --> 00:34:37,833
你根本没在听我说什么
You haven't heard a word I've been saying.

398
00:34:38,202 --> 00:34:39,792
没事吧？
Is everything all right?

399
00:34:39,802 --> 00:34:41,502
原谅我
Forgive me.

400
00:34:44,802 --> 00:34:46,842
那…你需要什么？
So what was it you needed?

401
00:34:48,801 --> 00:34:51,381
我想让艾瑞纳脱离奴籍，带她去乡下过日子
I want to free Eirene, take her off to the country,

402
00:34:51,401 --> 00:34:53,531
 如果你能借我点钱  当然可以
 if you'll lend me some money.  Of course.

403
00:34:53,601 --> 00:34:55,701
我还想让你陪我一起去奴役登记处
And I'll need you to come with me to the slave registry,

404
00:34:55,801 --> 00:34:57,591
用你的名字做我的担保人
 to vouch your name for my ownership.  Slow down. Why are you freeing Eirene?

405
00:34:57,591 --> 00:34:59,060
等一下，你为什么要让艾瑞纳脱离奴籍？

406
00:34:59,090 --> 00:35:00,440
如果她是奴隶我就不能娶她
 Can't marry her otherwise.  Marry her?

407
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,070
娶她？

408
00:35:04,730 --> 00:35:06,700
听着…我…
Look, I've--

409
00:35:06,770 --> 00:35:09,769
我最近…很消沉…
I've been feeling strange and low

410
00:35:09,829 --> 00:35:12,839
这几个月来一直是这个样子
and empty these last months, and...

411
00:35:14,869 --> 00:35:18,098
不管怎么样，我现在是想通了，我明白我为什么会这样了
anyway, I've puzzled it out, and I realized what it was.

412
00:35:19,498 --> 00:35:21,938
我爱艾瑞纳
I love Eirene.

413
00:35:21,998 --> 00:35:24,468
我爱她，我想和她一起拥有我们的孩子
I love her, and I want her to bear my children

414
00:35:24,528 --> 00:35:26,498
让她做我的妻子…
and be my wife, and...

415
00:35:31,667 --> 00:35:33,737
我想我只能说恭喜了…
Congratulations, I suppose.

416
00:35:36,697 --> 00:35:40,316
那么…你说你要去乡下？
So you'll be going to the country, you say?

417
00:35:41,166 --> 00:35:43,106
要离开罗马？
Leaving Rome?

418
00:35:43,166 --> 00:35:44,706
罗马不是我应该呆的地方
Rome's no place for me.

419
00:35:44,766 --> 00:35:47,435
我需要新鲜的空气，自由的空间
I need clean air, room to move.

420
00:35:47,955 --> 00:35:50,265
那么你到了乡下打算靠什么谋生？
And what will you do when you get there?

421
00:35:50,735 --> 00:35:52,835
一个强壮的男人到哪都能有口饭吃
There's always work for a good man with a sword.

422
00:35:53,665 --> 00:35:55,805
好吧，既然你已经打定主意了…
Well, as long as you're sure.

423
00:35:58,864 --> 00:36:00,604
我都考虑清楚了
Oh, I've thought it through.

424
00:36:01,364 --> 00:36:03,664
我这辈子从来没有这么肯定过
I've never been so sure of anything in my life.

425
00:36:05,204 --> 00:36:07,563
我为你高兴
I'm happy for you.

426
00:36:08,243 --> 00:36:10,233
希望你找到自己生活的路
I hope you find your path.

427
00:36:15,903 --> 00:36:17,432
怎么还呆在这里？
Still here? I thought you were

428
00:36:17,582 --> 00:36:20,472
我还以为你已经为了你的尊严隐居乡下了呢
retiring to the country as a point of honor.

429
00:36:20,532 --> 00:36:22,332
你尽可以嘲笑我
You do right to mock me.

430
00:36:22,642 --> 00:36:24,812
你让我感到渺小
You make me feel small.

431
00:36:24,852 --> 00:36:26,142
开个玩笑，老人家，只是个玩笑
A joke, old man, a joke. I'm always happy for your company.

432
00:36:26,142 --> 00:36:27,931
有你在我总是感到快乐

433
00:36:28,001 --> 00:36:31,661
那么…你为什么不事先告诉我
So, why didn't you tell me beforehand?

434
00:36:31,701 --> 00:36:33,331
我至少可以给你提供一点帮助
I could have been of assistance perhaps.

435
00:36:33,401 --> 00:36:34,741
你在说什么？
What are you talking about?

436
00:36:35,701 --> 00:36:38,190
所有人都在看这个
Everyone is reading it!

437
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:41,170
我从神殿里的女奴那拿到的抄本
I saw some temple prostitutes with a copy.

438
00:36:42,370 --> 00:36:44,370
“觉醒吧！道德”
"A call to virtue."

439
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:46,699
文章本身是没有什么问题
The writing is... adequate, which is something

440
00:36:46,769 --> 00:36:48,799
只是有些地方我们得讨论一下，但是观点却是十分
we should talk about, but the sentiments are

441
00:36:49,069 --> 00:36:50,949
高贵和勇敢的
full of grace and bravery.

442
00:36:50,969 --> 00:36:53,769
共和国的子民，先辈的血液
"Sons of the Republic, the blood of our forefathers

443
00:36:53,839 --> 00:36:56,568
呼唤着你们不要遗忘过去，行动起来…
calls you to honor the memory and emulate the deeds

444
00:36:57,338 --> 00:36:59,958
波卡斯·卡托，最后一个真正的罗马人
of Porcius Cato, the last true Roman."

445
00:36:59,968 --> 00:37:01,908
谁写的这个？
Who wrote this?

446
00:37:01,968 --> 00:37:03,968
你写的
You did.

447
00:37:09,907 --> 00:37:11,607
神灵保佑我们！
Gods beneath us!

448
00:37:12,367 --> 00:37:13,887
母亲！！
Mother!

449
00:37:15,637 --> 00:37:16,706
母亲…你读过这个了吗？
Mother, have you seen this?

450
00:37:17,506 --> 00:37:20,436
这篇疯狂的东西？
This lunacy?

451
00:37:20,706 --> 00:37:21,836
我当然看过了
Of course I've seen it.

452
00:37:21,846 --> 00:37:23,246
这不是什么疯狂
It's not lunacy.

453
00:37:23,306 --> 00:37:26,875
这是在暴政的统治下
It is a cogent defense of Republican principles

454
00:37:26,905 --> 00:37:29,465
对共和国原则的扞卫
against the forces of tyranny.

455
00:37:30,295 --> 00:37:32,145
我为此感到骄傲
I am rather proud of it.

456
00:37:32,155 --> 00:37:33,575
是你写的？
You wrote this?

457
00:37:34,435 --> 00:37:36,174
用我的名义？
In my name?

458
00:37:36,184 --> 00:37:37,934
卡西亚斯
Cassius contributed

459
00:37:37,934 --> 00:37:39,934
给文章修饰了一下
several nice turns of phrase.

460
00:37:40,034 --> 00:37:41,974
你肯定认得卡西亚斯
You know Cassius, of course.

461
00:37:42,034 --> 00:37:44,454
很高兴见到你，当然
Of course. Delighted.

462
00:37:45,993 --> 00:37:47,493
昆特斯
Quintus.

463
00:37:48,123 --> 00:37:49,393
很高兴再次见到你
It's lovely to see you again.

464
00:37:49,403 --> 00:37:51,733
 好久不见了  是啊…
 It's been too long.  lndeed.

465
00:37:51,803 --> 00:37:53,763
请原谅…
You will excuse me

466
00:37:54,043 --> 00:37:56,602
我想和我妈妈私下谈谈
if I speak with my mother privately?

467
00:38:04,032 --> 00:38:06,271
我很抱歉让你失望了…
I'm deeply sorry you feel I have failed you,

468
00:38:06,341 --> 00:38:08,741
但是这也做的太过分了
but this- this is going too far.

469
00:38:08,801 --> 00:38:11,141
你不能就这样用我的名义…
My name is not yours to be used--

470
00:38:11,201 --> 00:38:12,841
你没有让我失望
You haven't failed me.

471
00:38:12,901 --> 00:38:14,870
你永远不会让我失望，因为我是你的母亲
You can't fail me, I'm your mother.

472
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:18,000
 你只是让共和国失望了  我的老天啊！
 You have failed the Republic.  Dear gods!

473
00:38:19,470 --> 00:38:21,240
把笔和纸给我拿来
Bring me a pen and paper. It's bad enough

474
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,340
让那个疯子腔昆特斯

475
00:38:22,350 --> 00:38:25,049
留在这里已经够糟糕的了
that you keep that little madman Quintus in this house,

476
00:38:25,069 --> 00:38:27,139
但是这个！
but this- this!

477
00:38:30,809 --> 00:38:33,209
 我不知道我该如何向他解释  你为什么不跪下来
 I don't know what to tell him.  Why don't you

478
00:38:33,219 --> 00:38:35,928
亲吻他的脚，请求他的宽恕？
fall on your knees and kiss his feet and beg for mercy?

479
00:38:36,268 --> 00:38:38,208
 你过去曾经这样成功过  但你呢？
 It served you in the past.  But not you.

480
00:38:38,268 --> 00:38:41,148
也许你恳求的不够中肯
Eh? Perhaps you did not beg hard enough.

481
00:38:55,186 --> 00:38:56,236
你…
You...

482
00:38:57,066 --> 00:39:00,046
你明白吗…
you do understand...

483
00:39:02,206 --> 00:39:05,335
他也许会为了这个而杀了我？
he might have me killed for this?

484
00:39:08,735 --> 00:39:12,575
罗马已经沦落到了一个恶魔的手里
Rome has fallen into the hands of a corrupt monster.

485
00:39:12,635 --> 00:39:14,324
你
You, direct descendant

486
00:39:14,324 --> 00:39:16,334
作为共和国建立者

487
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,344
的直系后代
of the father of the Republic,

488
00:39:19,324 --> 00:39:21,834
应该做点什么
what do you do?

489
00:39:28,373 --> 00:39:30,483
你想让我怎么做？
What would you have me do?

490
00:39:30,573 --> 00:39:32,303
想想你父亲会怎么做吧？
What would your father have done?

491
00:39:32,313 --> 00:39:34,142
你的祖父会怎么做？
What would his father have done? Would they bend their knees

492
00:39:34,142 --> 00:39:36,422
他们会向一个暴君下跪吗？
 to a tyrant?  They would take account

493
00:39:36,622 --> 00:39:37,902
他们至少会
of the specific circumstan--

494
00:39:37,902 --> 00:39:39,342
审时度势…

495
00:39:39,402 --> 00:39:43,172
他们会象疯狗一样赶走这个暴君！
They would chase him out of the city like any mad dog.

496
00:39:43,441 --> 00:39:45,591
赶走他？
Chased him out?

497
00:39:46,811 --> 00:39:48,941
那么我应该如何做呢？
And how am l to do that exactly?

498
00:39:49,111 --> 00:39:51,471
你不是孤单一人
You would not be alone.

499
00:39:51,541 --> 00:39:53,740
啊，对，这个屋子里的这些人
Ah, these fine men in the house

500
00:39:53,810 --> 00:39:55,740
都非常优秀，这点我相信
are very very good. I am reassured.

501
00:39:55,810 --> 00:39:58,610
他们是很棒，还有其它许多人也很棒
They are good men. And there are many others,

502
00:39:58,670 --> 00:40:00,770
有头脑，有智慧的那些人
men of rank and wisdom.

503
00:40:01,820 --> 00:40:03,839
那可不是什么疯狗
It is not a dog gone mad.

504
00:40:03,909 --> 00:40:08,009
我宁愿疯狂也不愿玷污我们的名声
I would rather be mad than disgrace our name.

505
00:40:08,069 --> 00:40:10,169
别说了
No more!

506
00:40:10,409 --> 00:40:14,478
把你的那些追随者赶走
You send your fool henchmen away...

507
00:40:15,108 --> 00:40:17,308
忘了这件愚蠢的事情
and forget this insanity.

508
00:40:23,377 --> 00:40:26,337
 布鲁图斯  卡西亚斯，再见到你真的很高兴
 Brutus.  Ah, Cassius, it's lovely to see you,

509
00:40:26,407 --> 00:40:28,277
但是…如你所见…
but, as you can see--

510
00:40:28,297 --> 00:40:30,537
当然，请原谅我们擅自拜访
Of course, forgive the intrusion.

511
00:40:30,917 --> 00:40:32,936
也许我们应该改天拜访
Perhaps I may visit another time.

512
00:40:33,006 --> 00:40:34,946
很好，当然
Good. Certainly.

513
00:40:37,176 --> 00:40:39,406
在朱庇特石的名义下，你是一个罗马公民
On Jupiter's stone, you're a full Roman citizen,

514
00:40:39,436 --> 00:40:42,485
你愿意为这个男人列出这些他拥有的财产做担保吗？
and you attest to this man's ownership of listed property?

515
00:40:42,575 --> 00:40:44,135
当然，我愿意
I am. I do.

516
00:40:45,075 --> 00:40:47,075
在这里签字
Sign here.

517
00:40:51,045 --> 00:40:52,904
任何记号都可以了
Any kind of mark will do.

518
00:40:53,864 --> 00:40:56,074
我会写我自己的名字！
I can write my name as good as the next man.

519
00:41:04,743 --> 00:41:06,373
好了
Done.

520
00:41:08,003 --> 00:41:10,473
42,42号过来
42. 42 up.

521
00:41:19,872 --> 00:41:21,072
艾瑞纳
Eirene.

522
00:41:22,481 --> 00:41:24,171
过来，我想和你谈谈
Come over here. I want to talk to you.

523
00:41:25,411 --> 00:41:27,331
我让你们单独聊聊
I'll leave you to it.

524
00:41:32,210 --> 00:41:35,110
我刚去了奴隶登记处，你已经不在是我的奴隶了
I've been to the registrar of slaves. You're no longer my slave.

525
00:41:35,130 --> 00:41:35,980
你把我卖了？
You've sold me? Oh, please don't sell me.

526
00:41:35,990 --> 00:41:37,680
请别把我卖掉

527
00:41:37,740 --> 00:41:39,680
别把我送走，我求你了
Don't send me away. I beg you.

528
00:41:39,740 --> 00:41:41,669
我让你自由了
I'm setting you free.

529
00:41:42,709 --> 00:41:45,499
你自由了，你可以看看这里
You're free. It says so here.

530
00:41:49,239 --> 00:41:51,179
谢谢
Thank you.

531
00:41:51,239 --> 00:41:53,738
太谢谢你了，你是这个世界上最好的人
Thank you. You're the kindest man alive.

532
00:41:55,708 --> 00:41:57,918
我爱你，先生 我爱你，先生
I love you, sir. I love you, sir.

533
00:41:57,918 --> 00:42:00,358
这里有件衣服
Here. Here. It's a dress.

534
00:42:01,757 --> 00:42:02,757
拿去试试吧
Um, go try it on.

535
00:42:02,777 --> 00:42:04,517
让我们看看合不合适
Let's see how it looks.

536
00:42:26,255 --> 00:42:29,685
泰特斯·波罗先生我简直不知道应该如何感谢你
Titus Pullo, sir. I cannot thank you enough.

537
00:42:29,685 --> 00:42:32,304
谢我？为什么？
Thank me? What are you thanking me for, boy?

538
00:42:32,304 --> 00:42:33,064
你让她自由了
For freeing her. We have been saving to buy our freedom,

539
00:42:33,414 --> 00:42:35,664
我们一直在存钱打算为自己赎身

540
00:42:35,714 --> 00:42:38,624
但我们没想过一切来的是那么快
but we never- to happen so soon.

541
00:42:38,624 --> 00:42:40,713
这简直是上天赐给我们的礼物
I cannot tell you what a gift it is.

542
00:42:40,713 --> 00:42:42,653
你们一起存钱？你和艾瑞纳？
You've both been saving? You and Eirene?

543
00:42:42,653 --> 00:42:44,453
我们想过要用乌瑞纳斯
We thought to take the vorenus name as ours

544
00:42:44,453 --> 00:42:46,453
作为我们自由后的姓氏
when we became freedmen,

545
00:42:46,703 --> 00:42:49,583
但是艾瑞纳说必须以你的名义
but Eirene says it must be under your name

546
00:42:49,583 --> 00:42:51,372
她才做我的妻子
she becomes my wife.

547
00:42:54,502 --> 00:42:56,012
妻子？
Wife?

548
00:42:56,032 --> 00:42:57,242
我是说，法定的妻子
Legal wife, I mean.

549
00:42:57,242 --> 00:43:00,191
我们早就在心中结为夫妻了
We are already married in our hearts.

550
00:43:00,191 --> 00:43:02,691
艾瑞纳？我的艾瑞纳？
Eirene? My Eirene?

551
00:43:03,131 --> 00:43:03,891
先生？
Sir?

552
00:43:05,371 --> 00:43:06,351
先生？
Sir!

553
00:43:35,548 --> 00:43:36,638
死了？
 Dead?  Looks like.

554
00:43:36,648 --> 00:43:37,848
看起来是…
 What happened?  I killed him. I did it.

555
00:43:37,848 --> 00:43:39,398
怎么了？

556
00:43:39,398 --> 00:43:41,247
我杀了他，是我干的

557
00:43:41,307 --> 00:43:44,007
我知道，但是为什么，为什么要这么做？
I can see that, but why? Why did you do this?

558
00:43:44,017 --> 00:43:45,097
没所谓了
 It doesn't matter.  It does matter, though.

559
00:43:45,097 --> 00:43:46,097
怎么会无所谓
It matters to me. This boy was my property.

560
00:43:46,287 --> 00:43:47,637
这关系到我

561
00:43:47,637 --> 00:43:49,946
这家伙是我的财产

562
00:43:50,016 --> 00:43:52,376
 他激怒了我  他激怒了你？
 He angered me.  He angered you?

563
00:43:52,446 --> 00:43:54,616
他…他和艾瑞纳，他们是…
He- he and Eirene, they were--

564
00:43:56,116 --> 00:43:58,916
那又有关系？难道你以为她是处女吗？
So what does that matter? Did you think she was a virgin?

565
00:43:58,976 --> 00:44:00,715
她依然是你的，你可以拥有她
She's still yours to use as you wish.

566
00:44:01,175 --> 00:44:03,015
我爱她
I love her.

567
00:44:03,075 --> 00:44:04,745
你这就是爱的证明？
This is how you prove it?

568
00:44:04,815 --> 00:44:08,145
这可不是停尸房，随便让你杀人的地方
This is no charnel house to kill people as you want.

569
00:44:08,215 --> 00:44:10,614
这是我的房子，我的家！
This is my home. My home!

570
00:44:12,282 --> 00:44:14,250
Shh.

571
00:44:14,344 --> 00:44:17,314
你在我的孩子面前干出这样的事情？！
You do this violence before my children?!

572
00:44:17,384 --> 00:44:19,013
对不起…
I'm sorry.

573
00:44:25,043 --> 00:44:26,653
我会赔偿你的
I'll pay you back.

574
00:44:27,743 --> 00:44:29,942
你用什么来赔偿，你这个傻瓜
Pay me back with what, you damn fool?

575
00:44:30,012 --> 00:44:32,332
除了我给你的钱，你一无所有
You've got no money but what I've given you.

576
00:44:33,012 --> 00:44:34,412
但是请你…
But please...

577
00:44:36,342 --> 00:44:37,982
别叫我傻瓜
do not call me a fool.

578
00:44:38,042 --> 00:44:40,381
我就是要这么叫你，你这个傻瓜
I'll call you what I like. You're a damn fool.

579
00:44:40,451 --> 00:44:42,351
我不在乎钱…
I don't care about the money.

580
00:44:42,451 --> 00:44:44,911
但你这么做太失礼了
It's the disrespect.

581
00:44:44,981 --> 00:44:46,951
看看你都干了些什么，看看他！
Look at what you did! Look at him!

582
00:44:48,650 --> 00:44:50,580
也许你是对的
Maybe you're right.

583
00:44:50,950 --> 00:44:52,650
也许我是个傻瓜
Probably am a fool.

584
00:44:54,210 --> 00:44:56,550
永远都没有办法像你那么聪明
Never was a clever one like you.

585
00:44:56,610 --> 00:44:59,409
从来没有降过职，从来没有受过处罚，从来没有被关过禁闭
Never demoted, you, never flogged, never locked up.

586
00:44:59,479 --> 00:45:01,409
一直在往上爬
Straight to the top.

587
00:45:01,879 --> 00:45:03,649
看看现在的你
And here you are,

588
00:45:03,879 --> 00:45:06,249
穿着干净，漂亮的官袍
with your nice, clean, white toga.

589
00:45:06,309 --> 00:45:08,248
不管你内在是多么的肮脏
Lovely cloth, that.

590
00:45:08,248 --> 00:45:13,248
外表始终是那么的光鲜亮丽
Stays clean no matter how much you wade in the filth.

591
00:45:13,548 --> 00:45:15,128
想说什么就直说
 Speak your mind.  As you will.

592
00:45:15,128 --> 00:45:19,517
好吧，你曾经说过恺撒是个叛徒
Time was, you said Caesar was a rebel and a traitor.

593
00:45:20,617 --> 00:45:23,447
他给了你钱和土地，但是现在呢？
And now, today, he tosses you some coin and some farmland,

594
00:45:23,547 --> 00:45:24,887
他变成了共和国的救世主
and he's savior of the Republic, and you're kissing his royal ass.

595
00:45:24,987 --> 00:45:26,597
你在他面前极尽阿谀奉承之能事

596
00:45:28,516 --> 00:45:30,446
你给我站起来！
You stand up.

597
00:45:30,516 --> 00:45:33,476
站起来！站起来！
Stand up! Stand up!

598
00:45:34,516 --> 00:45:36,686
我不想和你打
I'll not fight you.

599
00:45:38,945 --> 00:45:40,885
那就滚！
Then go.

600
00:45:40,945 --> 00:45:42,945
离开这里，永远别回来！
Go and do not come back here.

601
00:45:52,114 --> 00:45:54,984
走，走，别回到这里来！
Go. Go! And do not come back here.

602
00:45:55,044 --> 00:45:57,753
艾瑞纳，我很抱歉，我很抱歉…
Eirene, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

603
00:46:02,013 --> 00:46:03,853
离她远点…
Stay away from her.

604
00:46:04,213 --> 00:46:06,113
好吧
Right.

605
00:46:08,782 --> 00:46:10,482
对不起…
Sorry.

606
00:46:15,552 --> 00:46:17,481
我完全不知情
I had no idea.

607
00:46:17,551 --> 00:46:19,031
我要走了
I must go now.

608
00:46:19,781 --> 00:46:20,861
你…
You- you do believe me?

609
00:46:20,861 --> 00:46:22,701
你相信我？

610
00:46:22,711 --> 00:46:24,671
我亲爱的朋友，我当然相信你
My dear friend, of course I believe you.

611
00:46:24,691 --> 00:46:26,291
你从来不会对我撒谎
You have never lied to me.

612
00:46:26,311 --> 00:46:28,300
除此之外，为什么你要把你的名字签上去
Besides, why would you put your name to a thing

613
00:46:28,300 --> 00:46:30,190
 然后又否认呢？ 是的，正是如此
 and then deny it?  Well, exactly.

614
00:46:30,710 --> 00:46:33,920
但是任何人都可以利用我的名字
And anyone- anyone may forge my name to a thing

615
00:46:33,980 --> 00:46:35,780
来使某些东西招人耳目
to give it weight.

616
00:46:36,020 --> 00:46:38,779
我想我们必须开始习惯
We shall just have to become used to it, no doubt.

617
00:46:38,849 --> 00:46:42,719
我很想知道是谁写的
I wonder who it was that wrote it.

618
00:46:42,979 --> 00:46:45,179
我也是
I wish I knew.

619
00:46:46,119 --> 00:46:48,878
一定是个有天赋的人 我还真是很少见到
Someone of talent. Anyhow, I've seldom seen

620
00:46:48,948 --> 00:46:50,888
能够把一件坏事表述得如此好的人呢
a bad case so well put.

621
00:46:50,948 --> 00:46:52,678
也许我该回击他
I shall have to write a reply.

622
00:46:52,748 --> 00:46:56,318
其实，只要你跟我能够明白我们的立场
Well, as long as you and I know where we stand.

623
00:46:56,387 --> 00:46:58,537
我们的立场？
Where do we stand?

624
00:47:00,147 --> 00:47:02,087
我希望我们还是最好的朋友？
I hope we are the best of friends. Are we?

625
00:47:02,147 --> 00:47:04,087
当然，我们当然是
We are, we are.

626
00:47:04,147 --> 00:47:09,186
布鲁图斯，我从来没有质疑过你的友谊和忠诚
Brutus, I have never doubted your friendship or fidelity.

627
00:47:11,186 --> 00:47:13,186
即便是我们互相对立的时候
Even when we were enemies.

628
00:49:56,649 --> 00:49:58,139
泰特斯·波罗
Titus Pullo.

629
00:49:59,249 --> 00:50:01,389
你看起来疲惫极了
You look tired, my friend.

630
00:50:01,409 --> 00:50:02,489
我喝醉了
 I'm drunk.  These are hard times for war veterans.

631
00:50:02,489 --> 00:50:05,028
现在，战场上的老兵不吃香了

632
00:50:05,028 --> 00:50:07,768
你说得对
You're right there.

633
00:50:07,798 --> 00:50:09,598
太多的士兵回到罗马
Too many soldiers back in Rome.

634
00:50:09,608 --> 00:50:12,758
却没有那么多的工作，世道真是不行了
Not enough work to go round. It's a sad situation.

635
00:50:12,818 --> 00:50:14,317
有你这样的好身手
But it's a crime

636
00:50:14,457 --> 00:50:17,957
却流离失所，简直是罪过
to see a man of your ability unemployed.

637
00:50:20,117 --> 00:50:22,127
我很好
I'm doing fine.

638
00:50:23,356 --> 00:50:25,356
我有一身的本领
I have plenty of irons in the fire.

639
00:50:26,756 --> 00:50:28,726
如果你的抱负没有办法实现
Well, if your prospects don't work out,

640
00:50:28,786 --> 00:50:30,886
你可以去艾文泰大街上找一下
you can ask on any street in the Aventine

641
00:50:30,956 --> 00:50:32,925
易拉斯泰斯·福曼
for Erastes Fulman.

642
00:50:34,125 --> 00:50:36,225
我这有适合你的工作
I will always have a job for you.

643
00:50:37,225 --> 00:50:39,925
我是个士兵，不是杀手
I'm a soldier, not a murderer.

644
00:50:41,255 --> 00:50:45,124
在这个时代，这两种人，有区别么？
These days, Pullo, is there really any difference?

645
00:50:47,984 --> 00:50:49,984
这杯算我的
Have a drink on me.

646
00:50:50,124 --> 00:50:52,424
等你清醒了以后，可以来找我
When you've sobered up, come and see me.

647
00:50:52,593 --> 00:50:54,823
我们可以谈点生意
We'll talk a little business.

648
00:00:03,548 --> 00:00:06,548
翻译:TLF字幕组
